26566421,https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/26566421,Luxury Loft Penthouse! 20' Ceilings & Water views!,"Walk out of my brand new, ultra modern, luxury two story loft located in the center of the highest rated neighborhood in San Diego, Little Italy. The streets are lined with trees, cafés, the highest rated restaurants, eclectic bars, and local breweries.  You can walk to the Zoo, Waterfront Park, the convention center and more.  You'll absolutely love the large updated kitchen, light, and coziness.  Great for couples, solo travelers, and families.   Spacious and fully stocked with everything!","Unique is an understatement!  The ceiling heights, the loft sleeping area, and the private balcony, and the pricing are what makes my space the best by far.  The unit is exactly as pictured. There are 6 beds available - 1 in the loft area (up the ladder) 1 in the sofa bed, and 1 air mattress. The unit is located on the top floor - several sets of stairs are before the unit so unfortunately this is not a handicap accessible space as there is no elevator. You can access every part of the unit as well as the large common area roof deck at the top of the stair tower.","Walk out of my brand new, ultra modern, luxury two story loft located in the center of the highest rated neighborhood in San Diego, Little Italy. The streets are lined with trees, cafés, the highest rated restaurants, eclectic bars, and local breweries.  You can walk to the Zoo, Waterfront Park, the convention center and more.  You'll absolutely love the large updated kitchen, light, and coziness.  Great for couples, solo travelers, and families.   Spacious and fully stocked with everything! Unique is an understatement!  The ceiling heights, the loft sleeping area, and the private balcony, and the pricing are what makes my space the best by far.  The unit is exactly as pictured. There are 6 beds available - 1 in the loft area (up the ladder) 1 in the sofa bed, and 1 air mattress. The unit is located on the top floor - several sets of stairs are before the unit so unfortunately this is not a handicap accessible space as there is no elevator. You can access every part of the unit as well","If you want a neighborhood feel without all of the tourist traps, then Little Italy is the place for you.  My place is a couple blocks away from Ballast Point, Born & Raised, Cloak and Pedal, fine dining with celebrity chefs and Top Chef Winner, Brian Malarkey and Richard Blais...and a TON more options that I know you'll love.","There is a common area staircase that will lead you directly to your unit. The building has several flights of stairs, so take caution. PLEASE NOTE: This is an urban setting located within a very busy intersection near an interstate exit/entrance – due to it being a densely populated area with flight paths nearby, outside noise is to be expected and is typical for the area. Light sleepers may be bothered by the air traffic - there are approx. 6 flights passing over at night.","Once you're in Little Italy, you wont want to leave.  Just in case you do,  the airport is about 5 minutes drive, the convention center is about 10 minutes drive or 20 minutes on the Green Line trolley, and the closest beaches (Ocean Beach or Coronado beach) are about 10 minutes away. There is no parking on the property, but there is free street parking along State street, which is less than a block away that does not require a permit.  There is also a paid parking lot one block away on the corner of Hawthorn and Columbia Street. Vehicles should be parked no further than 18” from the curb. Blocking of any driveway is not allowed. I do recommend using Uber or Lyft to get around as to avoid the hassle of parking during your stay - as with any highly populated city, sometimes it can be challenging. The area is extremely walkable with a walk score of 97, and the green line trolley is nearby.",You can access every part of the unit as well as the large common area roof deck at the top fo the stair tower.  It's a beautiful view of the San Diego Bay at sunset and it's super fun to watch the planes fly into San Diego International Airport.,"Being that I am a local San Diegan, I am more than happy to give you recommendations on restaurants, bars, beaches, and other fun activities that will make your stay one to remember.  Just let me know what you like and I'll be happy to guide you in the right direction.",- Smoking only allowed on balcony space with door closed.   - Please be mindful of noise after 10:00pm. - Guest visitors are welcome; loud parties are not. - Please dispose of all used biological products prior to check out.,,198870547,https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/198870547,Jessica,6/29/2018,"San Diego, California, United States","I'm a thirty something financial professional with a background in, dance, world travel, and sandy beaches.  I'm originally from San Diego and have lived in the downtown area for the past 6 years.  I am big-time foodie and love a good cocktail, which is why I chose to live in the heart of Little Italy's diverse bar and culinary scene.  I travel half of my time for work but when I am home I enjoy every part of Little Italy.  I'm a fan of all things indie (films, music), an avid reader, and a technophile.  I'm also a fan of classic rock (Beatles, Stones, Petty, Eagles, Clapton, Skynyrd, Fleetwood Mac, etc.) and enjoy all types of live music whenever possible. 

The late Anthony Bourdain is and will always be a hero of mine.  Traveling and exploring new cities is my true calling in life, and the best way to do that is often by staying in the neighborhoods you want to see, hear, and feel.  I love the experience Airbnb gives -- making you feel at home instead of displaced.",within an hour,100%,,f,Little Italy,8.0,8.0,t,f,"San Diego, CA, United States",Little Italy,Little Italy,San Diego,CA,92101.0,San Diego,"San Diego, CA",US,United States,32.72476,-117.16838,t,Loft,Entire home/apt,4,1.0,0.0,2.0,Real Bed,"{TV,""Cable TV"",Wifi,""Air conditioning"",Kitchen,Heating,Washer,Dryer,""Smoke detector"",""Carbon monoxide detector"",""First aid kit"",""Safety card"",""Fire extinguisher"",Essentials,Shampoo,Hangers,""Hair dryer"",Iron,""Laptop friendly workspace"",""Self check-in"",Lockbox,""Private entrance"",Bathtub,""Window guards"",""Hot water"",""Bed linens"",""Extra pillows and blankets"",Microwave,""Coffee maker"",Refrigerator,Dishwasher,""Dishes and silverware"",""Cooking basics"",Oven,Stove,""Patio or balcony"",""Wide entrance for guests"",""Well-lit path to entrance"",""Wide doorway to guest bathroom"",""Wide clearance to shower, toilet"",""Wide entryway""}",,$150.00 ,$150.00 ,$0.00 ,$90.00 ,2,$15.00 ,1,31,73,146,7/12/2018,8/11/2019,High,f,t,f,strict_14_with_grace_period,f,f
35234793,https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/35234793,"Central 6bd 4Ba with 5 parking spots, Wifi, AC","Feel like a local & enjoy all that San Diego has to offer. The airport & many of central SD's hottest neighborhoods & sightseeing are less than 10 minutes away. The beaches of Coronado are a short drive away over the adjacent landmark Coronado Bridge, other attractions such as Balboa Park, Petco Park, the Zoo, Gaslamp Quarter, Little Italy, South Park, North Park and more are a stone's throw away.","You'll be in an urban up and coming neighborhood with working families and a lively main avenue one block over so there is a possibility you will hear various street noises during the day and at night.   We offer amenities such as: Keurig Coffee maker with some starter coffee pods, High speed WiFi, Samsung Smart TVs with available access to Amazon and Netflix streaming (*with a valid log in). There is a fully functioning kitchen with full sized stainless steel appliances, fridge, microwave, dishwasher and toaster-oven. Dishes, glassware, silverware, pots and pans are also provided. Beds have fresh linen, towels are provided, and we offer body soap and shampoo and conditioner. There is an iron and ironing board, and although San Diego has mild weather year round, the home offers both heat/AC in the living room, personal heaters in each room for the cooler nights, and ceiling fans in every room for the warmer ones.  CHECK IN: There is keyless entry with a personal guest code, which allow","Feel like a local & enjoy all that San Diego has to offer. The airport & many of central SD's hottest neighborhoods & sightseeing are less than 10 minutes away. The beaches of Coronado are a short drive away over the adjacent landmark Coronado Bridge, other attractions such as Balboa Park, Petco Park, the Zoo, Gaslamp Quarter, Little Italy, South Park, North Park and more are a stone's throw away. You'll be in an urban up and coming neighborhood with working families and a lively main avenue one block over so there is a possibility you will hear various street noises during the day and at night.   We offer amenities such as: Keurig Coffee maker with some starter coffee pods, High speed WiFi, Samsung Smart TVs with available access to Amazon and Netflix streaming (*with a valid log in). There is a fully functioning kitchen with full sized stainless steel appliances, fridge, microwave, dishwasher and toaster-oven. Dishes, glassware, silverware, pots and pans are also provided. Beds have ","The neighborhood is an up and coming area surrounded by a colorful ethnic vibe. Although there are some things within a minimal walking distance, our neighboring barrios take a little more stamina. Chicano Park, in the middle of Barrio Logan, is about a mile distance. South Park, a small but sweet established neighborhood, is also about a mile distance with the closest, and perhaps the smallest, Target. This area boasts a great Vegan restaurant, one of our favorite Italian restaurants, and a fun beer bar that has an array not usually seen. If you’re in town for a baseball game or major event at Petco Park then that will only be 1.5 miles away, making it very convenient to get to. Some other great spots within a short enough distance are Dark Horse Coffee, Mutual Friends Ice Cream shop (try the banana chocolate peanut butter cup) Turf Club (grill your own steak) and Counterpoint (with gastro pub type fare), Tajima East Village is great for Ramen, Punch Bowl Social is a fun recreational ","VERY IMPORTANT: The home is a duplex and therefore has shared walls and floors. Please keep this in mind as loud noise and footsteps can travel between units. We ask that you respect quiet hours (after 10pm and before 7am) to ensure all guests have an equally enjoyable time in the home. Thanks in advance for your cooperation in respecting the other guests and neighbors.  There is NO smoking allowed in the property, it is only allowed in the designated backyard area away from the house (NOT in the attached patio). Please make sure to clean up after yourself or an additional cleaning fee will be incurred for cigarette butt littering. If the house is odiferous of cigarettes due to smoking in the attached patio, a fee may be incurred for removal of the smell.  San Diego is a fantastic place to visit. We love our home and take pride in it. Please be considerate of the neighbors and understand they are not on vacation. Please respect the property and treat it as if it were your own home. And","TRANSPORTATION: The trolley stops are conveniently two blocks away. Downtown and the convention center are just a five-minute drive or two stops by trolley. We have all the conveniences of city exploring by way of Uber, Lyft, Bird scooters, and rental bikes (Lime, etc.)",You will have access to the entire two story unit and backyard. All parking will be accessible as well.,We live on premise and are available through the Air BNB app or by telephone directly in case of emergency. Sometime we are available to meet you and other times we are not so we have easy self check in instructions sent on the day of and sometime the day before arrival.,"Check-in Time is 3pm or 1500 and Checkout time is 11am  This is a residential area. Please be a respectful neighbor and keep the noise down to a reasonable level, especially during quiet hours. Quiet hours are 10pm-8am M-F and 11pm-8am Sat & Sun +Holidays Please respect the home as your own and No shoes in the house All types of Smoking is not allowed inside the house.",,110555724,https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/110555724,Nelly,1/8/2017,"San Diego, California, United States","I am a 38 y/o traveler that is open minded and likes adventure, exploring other countries, and soaking up culture (especially food :)). I consider myself to be respectful of people's space and treat their home as if it were my own. I currently work as a nurse and have had many life experiences by way of working at a young age, to joining the military and a whole bunch else in between. I haven't made the chance to travel and am focused on changing that and getting out to see new things. ",within an hour,98%,,t,Grant Hill,9.0,9.0,t,f,"San Diego, CA, United States",Grant Hill,Grant Hill,San Diego,CA,92102.0,San Diego,"San Diego, CA",US,United States,32.70769,-117.13141,t,House,Entire home/apt,16,4.0,6.0,8.0,Real Bed,"{TV,Wifi,""Air conditioning"",Kitchen,""Free parking on premises"",""Free street parking"",Heating,Washer,Dryer,""Smoke detector"",""Carbon monoxide detector"",""First aid kit"",""Fire extinguisher"",Essentials,Shampoo,""Lock on bedroom door"",Hangers,""Hair dryer"",Iron,""Self check-in"",Keypad,""Private entrance"",""Pack ’n Play/travel crib"",""Hot water"",Microwave,""Coffee maker"",Refrigerator,Dishwasher,""Dishes and silverware"",""Cooking basics"",Oven,Stove,""BBQ grill"",""Patio or balcony"",""Garden or backyard""}",,$500.00 ,$500.00 ,"$2,500.00 ",$450.00 ,16,$0.00 ,2,40,2,4,7/21/2019,7/28/2019,Very High,f,f,f,flexible,f,f
35263191,https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/35263191,"FIESTAISLAND,MISSION BAY, BALBOA PRK CLOSE AC/ W&D","Suggested Ritual: Wake Up to Fresh Roasted Ground Coffee at nearby Coffee Shop, steps away from this unit.  While there, plan if you want to go to: (a) Walk/Run @ Mission Bay (1 Mile Away) (b) Have Breakfast in Old Town - 1.3 Miles away (c) Go to Sea World - 1.7 Miles, Go to Pacific Beach - 3.3 Miles (d) Visit Balboa Park - 4.7 Miles (e) Go to the Zoo - 6 Miles away (f) Downtown San Diego - 5.7 Miles (g) Visit La Jolla 7.8- Miles (h) Check Out Coronado (i) ...relax in your room watching Smart TV","Unique Concept -Enjoy the breeze from Mission Bay, located just 1 mile away - Minutes from Downtown, SD Zoo, Sea World, Balboa Park close by.  8 miles to la Jolla, Coronado 9 miles away. USD 1 mile  Your Space JUST OPENED 3.27.19 AFTER EXTENSIVE 14 MONTH REMODEL! - It pleases us to share with you what our guests are saying… Property has several size units, so please check the reviews in Context and check that the unit that you are interested in has capacity for your number of guests…. “Very nice 3 bedroom place in a nice area. Very comfortable for a family of 6. Very close to Sea World. Check in and out was very easy.” - Al (April 2019) “Great and stylish place. Wish we could’ve stayed longer but the room was very clean and new. Close to everything we wanted to enjoy in San Diego” - Sylvester (April 2019) “Excellent location if you're planning to travel to Sea World.” - Enrique (April 2019) “Amazing location and price. You can’t beat it. The unit is completely remodeled with all upscal","Suggested Ritual: Wake Up to Fresh Roasted Ground Coffee at nearby Coffee Shop, steps away from this unit.  While there, plan if you want to go to: (a) Walk/Run @ Mission Bay (1 Mile Away) (b) Have Breakfast in Old Town - 1.3 Miles away (c) Go to Sea World - 1.7 Miles, Go to Pacific Beach - 3.3 Miles (d) Visit Balboa Park - 4.7 Miles (e) Go to the Zoo - 6 Miles away (f) Downtown San Diego - 5.7 Miles (g) Visit La Jolla 7.8- Miles (h) Check Out Coronado (i) ...relax in your room watching Smart TV Unique Concept -Enjoy the breeze from Mission Bay, located just 1 mile away - Minutes from Downtown, SD Zoo, Sea World, Balboa Park close by.  8 miles to la Jolla, Coronado 9 miles away. USD 1 mile  Your Space JUST OPENED 3.27.19 AFTER EXTENSIVE 14 MONTH REMODEL! - It pleases us to share with you what our guests are saying… Property has several size units, so please check the reviews in Context and check that the unit that you are interested in has capacity for your number of guests…. “Very nic","Suggested Ritual: (a) Wake Up and walk to Bird Rock Coffee Roasters (1270 Morena Blvd), steps away from this unit.  While there, plan if you want to go to: (a) Walk/Run @ Mission Bay (1 Mile Away) (b) Have Breakfast in Old Town - 1.3 Miles away (c) Go to Sea World - 1.7 Miles (d) Visit Balboa Park - 4.7 Miles (e) Go to the Zoo - 6 Miles away (f) Downtown San Diego - 5.7 Miles (g) Visit La Jolla 7.8- Miles (h) Check Out Coronado","Towels are included (1 per occupant, make sure you notify us of exact guest count when making your reservation). Unit is complete with Dining Ware (plates, cups, glasses), Silverware (forks, knives, etc), Microwave Oven, countertop hot plate, Coffeemaker (drip style, with mesh filter), Blender, Toaster, Washer + Dryer, Ironing Board, Iron. Bath has Hair Dryer.   CONSUMABLES (PLEASE READ): Prior to your arrival, we refill hand soap bottles and provide (1) roll of toilet paper per bedroom. We DO NOT clean/service/restock the units every day. Please be aware of this upon arrival,so you can be prepared and obtain the consumables for your (a) number of guests and (b) The length of your stay.  (Consumables = toilet paper, shampoo, laundry detergent, sponges, cooking oil, trash bags, etc). Units are cozy due to having many amenities (washer+dryer, Kitchenette) in a SMALL footprint.  PLEASE NOTE THESE ARE 2 ADJACENT ROOMS, THEY DO NOT SHARE AN INTERIOR DOOR, BUT ARE RIGHT NEXT TO EACH OTHER. C","Located Right on California’s Historic 101 Route, Property is easily accessible by Bus (Bus Stop in front of this property), Trolley 1.3 Miles (Old Town Station), Rideshare Services (Uber, Lyft). You can Walk to Mission Bay, located just 1 mile away.",All areas of the units are available for guest access.,"Feel Free to Contact us 24/7 thru Airbnb messaging app, we have a team ready to assist you.",Quiet Hours from 9PM to 8AM,,26542025,https://www.airbnb.com/users/show/26542025,Mario,1/22/2015,"San Diego, California, United States","Welcome to our Home! Whether you visit Sunny San Diego for a day or longer, from nearby cities to continents apart, I want to make sure that you enjoy our beautiful town and make your stay as relaxing and uncomplicated as possible. And if anything arises, please, let us know.

